<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Jones, John. Letter to Judge Adam Mabane, 1787, with a copy of Jones's testimony 1783. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0003</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p><span class="fw">4</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="DelHand-author">is a fact of a very Serious and important Nature</span>.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">For a Judge <span class="DelHand-author">by  <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span>, to attempt to deprive the Commerce of the great and admired privilege of Trial by Jury in Civil and Commercial Actions (which His Majesty had recommended &amp; injoined as a Duty upon His Council to grant, &amp; which was granted to the great Comfort and satisfaction of the people) is <span style="text-decoration:underline;">a fact of a very serious &amp; important Nature</span>.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">For a judge <span class="DelHand-author">by <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> to urge the people to the painful necessity of applying to the Legislative Council for relief against his Measures <span class="DelHand-author">&amp; <span class="Gap">[&#8230;]</span></span> &amp; thereby to cause a<span class="DelHand-author">n</span> <span class="AddHand-author">public </span>investigation into his Conduct, is <span style="text-decoration:underline;">a fact of a very serious and important Nature</span>.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">For a Judge to frame or countenance an Ordinance that in Civil &amp; Commercial Actions, he shall put interrogatories to the parties <span class="AddHand-author">which may </span><span class="DelHand-author">to</span> condemn themselves, <span class="AddHand-author">&amp;</span> which they must answer, or <span class="DelHand-author">it</span> <span class="AddHand-author">the Law</span> is nugatory <span class="DelHand-author">to put them</span>, is <span style="text-decoration:underline;">a fact of a very serious &amp; important Nature</span>.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="DelHand-author">For a Judge to be framing <span class="AddHand-editors">[&#8230;]</span> peoples Property at risk, is a fact of a very serious &amp; important Nature.</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">For a Judge to be framing or countenancing Ordinances</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">JJ</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[13]</span></p>

